div.span:
The final analytics base table demonstrates the injection information for every production well.
Each row represents information for a single production well's data in a single day (the one that collects the bitumen mixture.
The days must include the Date feature in Production (primarily), along with the Well Test and Injection Data.
Note there overall in Wells between the Production and Well Test Datasets, but not with the injection data. This is obviously because of the unique SAGD process.
The blue section represents the metered steam levels of all the injector wells in the field, although not all of them communicate with the specific production well. Anyways, all the metered steam data will be recorded as per the date, not the production well!
The purple section represents the name of the production well, it's pump speed, and sensor information for that particular date.
The green section refers to how much oil, water, and fluid (etc.) was collected by the production well on that particular day. There might not always be data here since well testing didn't happen every day (only happened sometimes).
The pink section represents the average temperature along a specific spatial segment of the liner for specific day. This is condensed from an initially much larger dataset.
